        <content type="html" xml:base="https://harper.rocks/writing-music-with-purpose/">&lt;h2 id=&quot;introduction&quot;&gt;Introduction&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When begginers first get into music, people often tell them to learn things like scales, harmony and theory in general.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While music theory ir &lt;strong&gt;VERY&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; useful and necessary and you definetly should study it, sometimes it is like telling someone learning to draw to study anatomy before they even learn how to draw lines.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Though knowledge is never a waste of time - someone who understands anatomy can probably draw humans better than someone who knows nothing at all - when you&#x27;re looking for results it can really hold you back.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;the-musical-language&quot;&gt;The Musical Language&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
